abstract: In the end, Joe Biden, who bills himself as the most electable candidate in the 2020 U.S. Democratic presidential field, could not convince nearly enough Iowans that he is the best person to take on President Donald Trump in November.
snippet: In the end, Joe Biden, who bills himself as the most electable candidate in the 2020 U.S. Democratic presidential field, could not convince nearly enough Iowans that he is the best person to take on President Donald Trump in November.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa — In the end, Joe Biden, who bills himself as the most electable candidate in the 2020 U.S. Democratic presidential field, could not convince nearly enough Iowans that he is the best person to take on President Donald Trump in November.
headline_main: Rosy Polls but Few Yard Signs: How Joe Biden Stumbled in Iowa
headline_print_headline: Rosy Polls but Few Yard Signs: How Joe Biden Stumbled in Iowa

abstract: FBI Director Chris Wray said Wednesday that Russia is engaged in “information warfare” heading into the 2020 presidential election, though he said law enforcement has not seen ongoing efforts by Russia to target America's election infrastructure.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — FBI Director Chris Wray said Wednesday that Russia is engaged in “information warfare” heading into the 2020 presidential election, though he said law enforcement has not seen ongoing efforts by Russia to target America's election infrastructure.
headline_main: FBI Director Warns of Ongoing Russian 'Information Warfare'
headline_print_headline: FBI Director Warns of Ongoing Russian 'Information Warfare'

abstract: Conservative U.S. Chief Justice John Roberts always looked unlikely to become the hero for liberals at President Donald Trump's Senate impeachment trial that some of them had hoped for. He turned out to be a mere bit player in the drama.

abstract: A 5-year-old boy from Guatemala who fractured his skull in an accident and suffered bleeding around his brain is not being properly treated at an immigration detention center in Texas for what could be a traumatic brain injury, family members and advocates alleged.
snippet: A 5-year-old boy from Guatemala who fractured his skull in an accident and suffered bleeding around his brain is not being properly treated at an immigration detention center in Texas for what could be a traumatic brain injury, family members and ...
lead_paragraph: HOUSTON — A 5-year-old boy from Guatemala who fractured his skull in an accident and suffered bleeding around his brain is not being properly treated at an immigration detention center in Texas for what could be a traumatic brain injury, family members and advocates alleged.
headline_main: Advocates Allege ICE Neglecting 5-Year-Old With Head Injury
headline_print_headline: Advocates Allege ICE Neglecting 5-Year-Old With Head Injury

abstract: Authors describe what it was like to work with the legendary Simon & Schuster editor, who died on Feb. 4.
snippet: Authors describe what it was like to work with the legendary Simon & Schuster editor, who died on Feb. 4.
lead_paragraph: The editor Alice Mayhew died on Tuesday at 87, leaving behind a legacy of best sellers and award-winning books. Some of the authors she worked with shared their memories of her.

abstract: SOMERSWORTH, N.H. — Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. on Wednesday unleashed direct and explicit attacks on Pete Buttigieg and Senator Bernie Sanders, both of whom he is badly trailing in partial Iowa caucus results, arguing that Mr. Sanders would drag down other Democratic candidates and chiding Mr. Buttigieg for playing down the accomplishments of the Obama administration.
lead_paragraph: SOMERSWORTH, N.H. — Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. on Wednesday unleashed direct and explicit attacks on Pete Buttigieg and Senator Bernie Sanders, both of whom he is badly trailing in partial Iowa caucus results, arguing that Mr. Sanders would drag down other Democratic candidates and chiding Mr. Buttigieg for playing down the accomplishments of the Obama administration.

abstract: Pete Buttigieg held a narrow lead over Bernie Sanders on Tuesday in long-delayed results from the chaotic Iowa Democratic Party caucuses, and former Vice President Joe Biden trailed badly in fourth place with about 71% of precincts reporting.
snippet: Pete Buttigieg held a narrow lead over Bernie Sanders on Tuesday in long-delayed results from the chaotic Iowa Democratic Party caucuses, and former Vice President Joe Biden trailed badly in fourth place with about 71% of precincts reporting.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa/LACONIA, N.H. — Pete Buttigieg held a narrow lead over Bernie Sanders on Tuesday in long-delayed results from the chaotic Iowa Democratic Party caucuses, and former Vice President Joe Biden trailed badly in fourth place with about 71% of precincts reporting.
headline_main: Buttigieg Has Narrow Iowa Lead on Sanders, Biden Lags in Democratic Race
headline_print_headline: Buttigieg Has Narrow Iowa Lead on Sanders, Biden Lags in Democratic Race

abstract: From excitement to embarrassment to full-on rage, Iowa Democrats who took part in the first of the state-by-state nominating contests in this year's U.S. presidential race ran the gamut of emotions as their quadrennial moment in the spotlight descended into chaos.
